caption: Great place!
I love California Tortilla! The staff here in Bethesda is my favorite location becuase of the staff. They are super amazing and add that extra touch.
Amazing vibes and super friendly service. The meals were fresh and delightful. Will definitely recommend this place to my friends. Affordable rates and big meals. Great work.

This restaurant is my favorite. I eat in plenty of restaurants but to this one I keep coming back again and again. The team is very cordial and the cuisine they offer is so good. I never decline to have a decent dinner in this place. I highly recommend this place.
Would surely recommend visiting this place. Awesome mood, flavorful dishes, great customer service. Great work.
We need more around

I always loved California tortilla, unfortunately because of covid you can’t choose your own spicy sauces. But you can request some at the register if you remember which one you liked. At this location once you get in you have to scan a QR code which makes you take a covid survey. The food is great and if you love food that has flavor you will love this restaurant. Some people compare it to chipotle but this place is better in my opinion. I love the Korean bbq (i choose the bowl version with tortilla on the side) . And its very affordable for the area.

Ordered a No-meato bowl, and the ingredients were slopped into the bowl in a most unattractive way. The veggies tasted like they spent 20 seconds in a microwave and they had a funky raw crisp and cooked hot spot texture. Most disappointing was the guac that tasted like a thick paste of lime juice. It was so sour! With all the good reviews, this was certainly unexpected.
Everyone is all was very nice. I don't think, I have ever had an issue.

Whenever we show up, the staff is courteous and welcoming. The food is good--there are delicious salads for me, burritos, etc. for others. It's healthy and not expensive and you don't have to wait too long for the food to be prepared as you watch. I appreciate how they're handling the pandemic. There have been a lot of changes on that street, but they are a rock. So grateful for CalTort.
Consistent food. Doing well considering circumstances (pandemic). Seems to be a bit of a bug problem in the bathrooms / hallways though
(Translated by Google) Great service! The delicious food.  (Original) Buen servicio! La comida deliciosa.
Good chips and great burritos

This place is definitely one of the most attractive restaurants in the area. Anytime I visit this place I am very pleased. They manage their high  standard service and the topmost level of cooking  they provide. You no doubt will love this restaurant. Warmly  recommended.

Always get my food prepared promptly and properly. The staff is nice and makes sure I get what I need. There's street parking there, across the street and around them in the neighborhood. They did kinda drop the ball on cinco de mayo this year. Accepting too many orders (online and in-store), not communicating with the dozens of people there waiting, ignoring those waiting at the registers looking for help, and not putting up  a notice that they were at capacity. You can expect places to be crowded during holidays but I also expect management to step up and keep the order. Having said that, the other times I've gone I've been happy with the food and service.

I visit this spot a lot since I work in the area. I got to say their customer service is always fantastic and they keep the spot well kept constantly. Pricing is convenient and they serve generous portions.

Would be 2 stars for the food isn't really that good, but added extra star because I accidentally took another persons food and the staff were really nice and understanding when I realized and went and told them.
Pretty good texmex but the burritos can be a bit soggy

This is one of my all-time favorite burrito places. I usually get the California screaming burrito and top it off with one of the many different hot sauces available on the wall the flame. I also enjoy the Coca-Cola machines that offer a dozen different Coca-Cola flavors at the touch of a button. The staff is always friendly and helpful and the facility is very clean. Keep up the good work!
Haven't been to a California tortilla for a LONG time! Had a bowl and loved it!

1st experience with California Tortilla and I approve! I had the California Screamin' burrito and it was pretty good. I forgot to order it without the fajita vegetables so I take responsibility for that mishap. The kids that were with me approved of their food as well. One ordered the Korean Bbq Burrito and the other ordered the Bbq Chicken Quesadilla. The service was prompt and friendly. The only downside was the Wall of Flame with too many sauces to choose from. It was hard to narrow it down to only one or two. I picked 3 I'd never tried before and 1 I've had a lot of times. I would visit California Tortilla again if I'm near one and in the mood for fresh Mexican food.

At the moment  you step in this restaurant  the personel give you an excellent feeling. Very friendly stuff, it is a nice restaurant to to go out with friends or with your date. heavenly  food, experienced  chef, competitive  price and excellent  service. Warmly recommended.
Food is always tasty and fast, the hot sauce selection is a highlight. Reasonably priced too.

Pros: Wall of flame (pictured), corn tortillas are default, fish texture was very good, fish weren't fishy, and they have the drink fountain with tons of options. The employees were friendly but not over-the-top (I could eat in peace). Cons: Tacos didn't have as much flavor as I'd expect, chicken pieces were a bit tough, and the Screamin' taco had a cheez-whiz-type cheese that detracted from the rest of the taco.

The food at California Tortilla in Bethesda is not only delicious it is also consistently fresh. I have also catered from California Tortilla on a number of occasions for my employees and not only is there great variety at an affordable price but the service and delivery is exceptional. My team loves when i cater from California Tortilla.

I have been eating at various California Tortilla's for about 12 years. Never disappoints. The Bethesda location is my favorite, and my meal of choice, the Blackened Chicken Caesar Burrito with chips and queso on the side. Getting hungry writing this actually...

I've used their catering for lunch meetings. What a nice change from deli sandwiches! They were great to work with to coordinate the catering order and delivery. Also, the attendees were very happy with the food. Made for a much more enjoyable gathering!

California Tortilla is a family favorite for easy school night dinners that offer a range of options for the vegetarians in the family.  Not only is it a hit with the kids, California Tortilla has catered lunches for our staff at work.  The burrito bar is a favorite and the CT staff are pleasant and very easy to work with.

The original California Tortilla location!!! Well, I guess not technically since years ago they expanded to a bigger location across the street, but you get the idea.  I've been eating here since I was 12 years old, and it's just as good now as it was then. My go to is the Honey Lime Burrito, but will sometimes get the Fajita Burrito with Chicken and add cheese.  You can't go wrong. It's good every single time. It's cheap, and it's about as fun as fast casual dining can possibly get.

Filthy establishment. My family ended up with food poisoning. The staff was very rude & the service was super slow. The staff was too busy talking to each other to pay proper attention to customers. I won't ever step foot in this place again.
Friendly staff and delicious food

My favorite part of eating here is the Wall if Flame, a collection of 50 odd hotsauces from around the world. They are rated in spiciness from 1 to 10. I thought I could handle a fair amount of heat, but 7 is my limit for this collection. The food itself is pretty standard for a fast casual chain restaurant.

Wife and I tried this place BASED SOLELY on Delvin Grant's review **below**.  Obviously, the chips and queso were ordered and they were delicious. Also had the blackened fish tacos...very tasty!  Definitely recommend!  Parking may be an issue when visiting...but if you work it out, enjoy!

One of my favorite places to stop for lunch in Bethesda. Usually easy to find parking and once inside the ordering process is smooth and food is prepared quickly.

If you don't mind waiting a little longer for your food to be prepared, I believe the quality and options at California Tortilla are much better than Chipotle. The Bethesda location was offering free ice cream when I visited.

Been going here for years as my cheap quick burrito/taco fix. Place has a nice setting. Always busy during the afternoons. Offers specials at this location sometimes. Don't forget the hot sauces on the "Wall of Flame." A staple for Bethesda on this side of town.

The food was good. Service was pretty fast. I tried the street Tacos and my wife had a bowl. The street Tacos I tried at other fast food places were dry, the tacos here were fresh and had a good ratio to tortialla to stuffing. The bowl is not your Chipotle bowl but it's decent. They have an interestingly big collection of sauces called the wall of flame about 70-75 unique sauces with different levels of spice. The premise itself is not the best, can be organized better and a little more appealing and clean.

Yummy food, fast funny and friendly employees You'll often see the actual owners working behind the counter themselves, making sure everyone is happy. I've never had a bad visit.

Live Cal-Tort just not this one.. Nachos were soggy, steak for my quesadilla had a lot of fat on it. Guac had been sitting in to go container overnight (see photo) terrible experience. Staff was ok.

Really delicious food. I craved Mexican food and found this place and it satisfied my appetite.  :) I also like that the staff is very friendly and courteous. Will definitely come here again.  Update: I've come here many times over the past year and I can definitely say that the staff and food has always been of great quality. It's definitely a good atmosphere for coming and sitting down with a group or even by yourself. Online ordering is a breeze too!

I'd wager others had a better experience than I did, and the place seemed popular enough, but it was the worst Mexican food experience I've ever had.  The place seemed nice enough, and the prices were decent, but the food was sub-par.  I ordered the BBQ burrito (I don't recall the exact name), which said it came with everything from ranch to beans to meat to BBQ sauce and rice. However, it seemed that it was mostly (70-80%) decent rice (I've made better) and a few dry pieces of meat. Next to zero BBQ or beans and no ranch flavor that I could find. It's the first burrito in my life that I've been unable to finish.  The chips were decent, but the guacamole was cheap and the salsa was appalling. It was little more than diced tomatoes and cilantro.  I think the worst part by far is the fact that it upset my stomach for nearly an hour afterwards and gave me trouble on the toilet, something that's never happened before (even with cheaper places like Taco Bell).  Hopefully others have better experiences.
